quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,70,"So they (too) hastened in their footsteps!"
  37,71,"And indeed most of the men of old went astray before them;"
  37,72,"And indeed We sent among them warners (Messengers);"
  38,49,"This is a Reminder. And verily, for the Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2) is a good final return (Paradise),"
  38,50,"‘Adn (Eden) Paradise (everlasting Gardens), whose doors will be opened for them."
  38,51,"Therein they will recline; therein they will call for fruits in abundance and drinks;"
  39,34,"They shall have all that they will desire with their Lord. That is the reward of Muhsinûn (good-doers - see the footnote of V.9:120)."
  39,35,"So that Allâh may expiate from them the evil of what they did and give them the reward, according to the best of what they used to do.{1}",1:[{39:35} See the footnote of {9:121}.]
  39,36,"Is not Allâh Sufficient for His slave? Yet they try to frighten you with those (whom they worship) besides Him! And whom Allâh sends astray, for him there will be no guide."
  40,13,"It is He Who shows you His Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) and sends down (rain with which grows) provision for you from the sky. And none remembers but those who turn (to Allâh in obedience and) in repentance (by begging His Pardon and by worshipping and obeying Him Alone and none else)."
  40,14,"So, call you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم and the believers) upon (or invoke) Allâh making (your) worship pure for Him (Alone) (by worshipping none but Him and by doing religious deeds sincerely for Allâh’s sake only and not to show off and not to set up rivals with Him in worship), however much the disbelievers (in the Oneness of Allâh) may hate (it)."
  40,15,"(He is Allâh) Owner of High Ranks and Degrees, the Owner of the Throne. He sends the revelation by His Command to any of His slaves He wills, that he (the person who receives revelation) may warn (men) of the Day of Mutual Meeting (i.e. the Day of Resurrection)."